{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer to cover personal debts. While embezzlement is a significant white-collar crime that requires a deterrent, modifying factors must be heavily heavily considered in sentencing. The defendant has no prior criminal record, demonstrating that this is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of criminal behavior. Furthermore, the defendant has already partially paid back the stolen funds, showing a commitment to making the victim whole and taking responsibility for their actions. Balancing the need for accountability with the mitigating factors of restitution and a previously clean record, a short period of incarceration followed by supervised probation and an order for full restitution is the most just outcome.",
  "verdict": 6
}
